{
  "id": "23",
  "name": "محاورۂ ما بین خدا و انسان",
  "+@BookID": "07",
  "bookName": "پیامِ مشرق",
  "+@SectionID": "02",
  "sectionName": "افکار",
  "Para": [
    {
      "name": "خدا",
      "Verse": [
        {
          "id": "01",
          "Text": [
            {
              "_content": "جہان را ز یک آب و گل آفریدم\nتو ایران و تاتار و زنگ آفریدی",
              "lang": "Original"
            },
            {
              "lang": "Urdu"
            },
            {
              "_content": "God: I made the whole world with the same water and clay, but you created Iran, Tartary, and Ethiopia.",
              "lang": "English"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "03",
          "Text": [
            {
              "_content": "من از خال پولاد ناب آفریدم\nتو شمشیر و تیر و تفنگ آفریدی",
              "lang": "Original"
            },
            {
              "lang": "Urdu"
            },
            {
              "_content": "From the earth I brought forth pure iron, but you made from that iron sword, arrow, and gun.",
              "lang": "English"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "05",
          "Text": [
            {
              "_content": "تبر آفریدی نھال چمن را\nقفس ساختی طایر نغمہ زن را",
              "lang": "Original"
            },
            {
              "lang": "Urdu"
            },
            {
              "_content": "You made an axe for the tree in the garden, and a cage for the songbird.",
              "lang": "English"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "name": "انسان",
      "Verse": [
        {
          "id": "07",
          "Text": [
            {
              "_content": "تو شب آفریدی چراغ آفریدم\nسفال آفریدی ایاغ آفریدم",
              "lang": "Original"
            },
            {
              "lang": "Urdu"
            },
            {
              "_content": "Man: You made the night, I made the lamp; you made the earthen bowl, I made the goblet.",
              "lang": "English"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "09",
          "Text": [
            {
              "_content": "بیابان و کہسار و راغ آفریدی\nخیابان و گلزار و باغ آفریدم",
              "lang": "Original"
            },
            {
              "lang": "Urdu"
            },
            {
              "_content": "You made deserts, mountains and valleys; I made gardens, meadows and parks.",
              "lang": "English"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "11",
          "Text": [
            {
              "_content": "من آنم کہ از سنگ آئینہ سازم\nمن آنم کہ از زہر نوشینہ سازم",
              "lang": "Original"
            },
            {
              "lang": "Urdu"
            },
            {
              "_content": "I am one who makes a mirror out of stone, and turns poison into sweet, delicious drink.",
              "lang": "English"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "id": 2
    }
  ],
  "name-en": "A Dialogue Between God And Man",
  "credits": "English Translation by: Mustansir Mir"
}